OL,3,CCornish school faces funding cuts as
OL,4,Csecond homes see pupil numbers dwindle
OL,6,FIt said as a result of fewer local
OL,7,Fchildren, it lost 17 pupils between
OL,8,Fthe 2022 and 2023 academic years,
OL,9,Fwhich equates to a loss in funding of
OL,10,F#100,000 from the Department for
OL,11,FEducation.JDr Jennifer Blunden, CEO of
OL,12,Fthe Truro and Penwith Academy Trust
OL,13,Fwhich Pendeen School belongs to, said
OL,14,Fthere is no immediate risk to the
OL,15,Fschool, its pupils or its staff but
OL,16,Fthe lack of uptake is indicative of a
OL,17,Flarger issue.JShe explained: "We have
OL,18,Fseen a shift as far as the number of
OL,19,Fpupils is concerned.
