OL,3,CCornish school faces funding cuts as
OL,4,Csecond homes see pupil numbers dwindle
OL,6,F"Pendeen School has lost 17 pupils and
OL,7,Fwith funding based on the number of
OL,8,Fpupils you have, that represents about
OL,9,F#100,000 which is a huge amount for a
OL,10,Flittle school.J"Pendeen is a lovely
OL,11,Fcommunity and our school is brilliant
OL,12,Fand we are working hard to make sure
OL,13,Fthe funding cut due to reduced pupil
OL,14,Fnumbers does not impact on the
OL,15,Feducation provision, but it does link
OL,16,Fto the shortage of low cost housing in
OL,17,Fthe area which is not taken up with
OL,18,Fsecond home ownership or holiday
OL,19,Flets."JThe drop in pupil numbers is
OL,20,Fdue to less uptake, and a bigger Year
OL,21,FSix group moving up to secondary
OL,22,Fschool.
